{"VOYAGE":[{"def":"Formerly, a passage either by sea or land; a journey, in general; but not chiefly limited to a passing by sea or water from one place, port, or country, to another; especially, a passing or journey by water to a distant place or country.","pos":""},{"def":"The act or practice of traveling.","pos":""}],"VOYAGEABLE":[{"def":"That may be sailed over, as water or air; navigable.","pos":""}],"VOYAGER":[{"def":"One who voyages; one who sails or passes by sea or water.","pos":""}],"VOYAGEUR":[{"def":"A traveler; -- applied in Canada to a man employed by the fur companies in transporting goods by the rivers and across the land, to and from the remote stations in the Northwest.","pos":""}]}